      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SUPERB VINTAGE (5) went to another level last start when winning by 1.2L in a BM44+ over 1300m here. The draw is the query, but she's clearly the one to beat off her latest effort. Can bring up the hat-trick today. ZAC LUVS TO FLY (3) missed narrowly last time out in a much stronger race at Bunbury last time out and looks well placed coming back to this grade. He's drawn to get his chance for Turner who knows the gelding well. Can put his best foot forward. SCREAM (2) held on to win in a photo finish at this track and trip last start. Tougher here, but the claim of Webster comes in handy and it wouldn't surprise to see him repeat the dose. TAWAAJ (7) comes back to a more suitable level today and can make her presence felt from a good draw. ORACLE SON (1) can return to form in this suitable race today.",
